# Git remote (not the default GitHub account)

This repo pushes to **naranjo135531-star**, not `nacosdev`. The machine default SSH key (`~/.ssh/id_rsa`) authenticates as `nacosdev` and will fail here.

## Repo config (already set locally)

- Remote: `git@github.com:naranjo135531-star/remote-scripts.git`
- SSH key: `~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo`
- Local override: `core.sshCommand = ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo -o IdentitiesOnly=yes`

## Push / pull

Use normal git commands from this repo — `core.sshCommand` forces the right key:

```bash
git push origin main
git pull origin main
```

Do **not** rely on the default SSH key or `gh` logged in as `nacosdev`.

## Verify SSH before push

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo -o IdentitiesOnly=yes -T git@github.com
# Expected: Hi naranjo135531-star!
```

If you see `Hi nacosdev!`, the wrong key is being used — set `IdentitiesOnly=yes`.

## If push fails with publickey

1. Confirm key fingerprint: `ssh-keygen -lf ~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo.pub` → `SHA256:R1ChryLKTTllHQadsXl50gNgj8sovI6MPzYDkD0EVm8`
2. Public key must be on **naranjo135531-star** → GitHub Settings → SSH keys (copy from `cat ~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo.pub` — base64 is case-sensitive)

## Optional ~/.ssh/config

```
Host github-naranjo
  HostName github.com
  User git
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed_naranjo
  IdentitiesOnly yes
```

Then: `git remote set-url origin git@github-naranjo:naranjo135531-star/remote-scripts.git`
